value.value: 胸郭の異常
any structural anomaly of the bony and cartilaginous structure enclosing the thoracic cavity, consisting of the thoracic vertebrae, ribs, costal cartilages, and sternum
助骨の付着異常
any anomaly in the normal joining of the ribs to the vertebral column or to the sternum
椎骨の圧迫
appearance of vertebrae that are flattened laterally along the whole length such that they appear pressed together and take up less rostrocaudal space
転子の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the bony prominences near the upper extremity of the femur; there are two in human (greater and lesser trochanters) and three in many other mammalian species (greater, lesser and third); these normally serve as attachment points for hip and thigh muscles
ダイテルス細胞の変性
degeneration or loss of the supporting cells of the spiral organ which are attached to the basement membrane and receive the hair cells between their free extremities
らせん蝸牛軸動脈の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the artery which parallels the spiral ganglion in the root of the spiral lamina of the modiolus, serving the ganglion and the cochlear duct and its contents
らせん蝸牛軸動脈の狭窄
abnormal narrowing or constriction of the artery which parallels the spiral ganglion in the root of the spiral lamina of the modiolus and serves the ganglion and the cochlear duct and its contents
聴覚皮質形態異常

any structural anomaly in the region of the cerebral cortex that receives the auditory radiation from the medial geniculate body, a thalamic cell group receiving auditory input from the cochlear nuclei in the rhombencephalon and is responsible for processing of auditory (sound) information

label.value: abnormal cochlear OHC efferent innervation pattern

value.value: 蝸牛OHC（外有毛細胞）の遠心神経支配異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear OHC efferent innervation pattern

value.value: any changes in the morphology or number of efferent terminals, occurring as clusters, in the cochlear OHC region; normally, medial olivocochlear neurons, which are primarily found in rostral and ventral periolivary regions, project mainly to the contralateral cochlea, and terminate directly on OHCs

label.value: abnormal cochlear IHC efferent innervation pattern

value.value: 蝸牛IHC（内有毛細胞）の遠心神経支配異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal cochlear IHC efferent innervation pattern

value.value: any changes in the morphology of the normally dense plexus of efferent terminals that contact radial fibers of the spiral ganglion below cochlear IHCs or of the sparser plexus of terminals positioned around IHC somata; normally, lateral olivocochlear neurons, which are found in and/or around the lateral superior olive, project mainly to the ipsilateral cochlea and terminate mostly on dendritic fibers below IHCs
中手骨の短縮
reduced length of the five bones of the forepaws that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges
中足骨の短縮
reduced length of the five bones of the hindpaws that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges
中手骨数の減少
reduced number of the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges
中手骨の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the metacarpal bones, typically resulting in decreased size
中手骨の伸長
increased length of the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges
中手骨の融合
improper union of one or more of the five bones of the forepaws/hands that articulate proximally with the carpal bones and distally with the phalanges
中足骨数の減少
reduced number of the five bones of the hindpaws/feet that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges
中足骨の伸長
increased length of the five bones of the hindpaws/feet that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges
中足骨数の融合
improper union of the five bones of the hindpaws/feet that articulate proximally with the cuneiform and cuboid bones of the tarsus and distally with the phalanges
椎骨数の異常
altered number of the bony segments of the spinal column
椎骨数の増加
an increase over the normal number of the bony segments of the spinal column
椎骨数の減少
a reduction from the normal number of the bony segments of the spinal column
頚椎数の減少
reduced number of the seven bony segments of the spine located anterior to the thoracic vertebrae and caudal to the skull
腰椎数の減少
reduced number of the six bony segments of the spine located anterior to the sacral vertebrae and posterior to the thoracic vertebrae
胸椎数の減少
reduced number of the thirteen bony segments of the spine located anterior to the lumbar vertebrae and posterior to the cervical vertebrae
仙椎数の減少
reduced number of the bony segments of the spine located posterior to the lumbar vertebrae and anterior to the caudal vertebrae
腰椎数の増加
increased number of the six bony segments of the spine located anterior to the sacral vertebrae and posterior to the thoracic vertebrae
胸椎数の増加
increased number of the thirteen bony segments of the spine located anterior to the lumbar vertebrae and posterior to the cervical vertebrae
尾椎の矮小化
reduced size of the bony segments of the coccyx or tail

definition.value: There are usually 27-30 caudal vertebrae present in rodents and only 3-5 fused caudal vertebrae in human.

value.value: 尾椎の欠損
absence of all of the bony segments of the coccyx or tail

definition.value: There are usually 27-30 caudal vertebrae present in rodents and only 3-5 fused caudal vertebrae in human.

value.value: 腰椎の欠如
absence of all of the six bony segments of the spine located anterior to the sacral vertebrae and posterior to the thoracic vertebrae
胸椎の欠如
absence of all of the thirteen bony segments of the spine located anterior to the lumbar vertebrae and posterior to the cervical vertebrae
仙椎の欠如
absence of all of the bony segments of the spine located posterior to the lumbar vertebrae and anterior to the caudal vertebrae
仙骨の矮小化
reduced size of any or all of the bony segments of the spine located posterior to the lumbar vertebrae and anterior to the caudal vertebrae

label.value: abnormal ventral tubercle of atlas morphology

value.value: 環椎の腹結節異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal ventral tubercle of atlas morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the conical ventral projection on the arch of the atlas
歯突起の異常
any structural anomaly of the large protuberance that projects upward from the cervical axis, around which the cervical atlas rotates
甲状腺濾胞細胞の欠如
absence of the thyroxine-producing follicular cells derived from the thyroid diverticulum which evaginates from the endodermal epithelium of the embryonic pharyngeal floor
甲状腺傍濾胞細胞の欠如

absence of the neuroepithelial secretory cells that occur singly or in small groups, close to the outer follicular borders but within the follicular basement membrane of the thyroid; these cells secrete calcitonin, 5-hydroxytryptamine and dopamine
甲状腺憩室の異常
any structural anomaly in the endodermal bud derived from the endodermal epithelium of the embryonic pharyngeal floor
無甲状腺症
congenital absence of the thyroid gland or suppression or absence of its hormonal secretion
内耳の発達遅延
slowed progression to structurally mature components of the labyrinth, including the semicircular canals, vestibule and cochlea
アブミ骨動脈の形態異常

any structural anomaly in the small artery that passes through the ring of the stapes; while the stapedial artery is a temporary artery thought to disappear at late embryonic stage in humans, the mouse stapedial artery is complete by E13 and persists into adulthood
アブミ骨動脈の欠如
absence of the small artery that passes through the ring of the stapes
椎体の発育不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the vertebral body, typically resulting in decreased size
椎体の欠如
absence of the main cylindrical portion of the vertebra ventral to the vertebral canal
椎体の肥大化
increased size of the main cylindrical portion of the vertebra ventral to the vertebral canal
椎体の矮小化
decreased size of the main cylindrical portion of the vertebra ventral to the vertebral canal
助骨の伸長
increased length of the bones forming the bony wall of the chest
助骨の短縮
reduced length of the bones forming the bony wall of the chest
外へ開いた助骨
any deviation from the normal curvature of the ribs such that the ribs are turned outward
